WEBVTT

00:09.642 --> 00:12.579
[tense music]

00:20.153 --> 00:23.256
[somber music]

00:24.824 --> 00:27.594
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:28.961 --> 00:32.332
[distant train rumbling]

00:32.365 --> 00:34.367
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:38.604 --> 00:39.739
[clank]

00:43.843 --> 00:44.811
Hey.

00:48.214 --> 00:49.382
Are you all right?

00:51.417 --> 00:53.585
All your stuff was gone,
so I thought--

00:53.619 --> 00:54.820
I'm fine.

00:54.853 --> 00:58.091
Well, what happened?
Did your sister do
something or...

00:58.858 --> 01:00.160
Henry, I'm leaving.

01:02.361 --> 01:04.230
-What?
-I can't stay here.

01:05.898 --> 01:08.468
Believe me,
I'm tempted.

01:08.501 --> 01:10.336
Even though the food
fuckin' sucks.

01:10.369 --> 01:12.705
You can't.
You can't.

01:12.738 --> 01:13.773
I need your help.

01:13.806 --> 01:15.074
-You don't.
-You're wrong.

01:15.107 --> 01:17.243
I fucked up.

01:17.277 --> 01:19.112
I fucked up like
you have no idea,

01:19.145 --> 01:21.247
and everything is worse,
and I can't.

01:21.281 --> 01:23.082
I can't.
I can't do this on my own.

01:23.115 --> 01:24.317
-Yes, you can.
-No.

01:24.350 --> 01:25.418
You can.

01:26.819 --> 01:28.254
You're stronger than you think.

01:30.056 --> 01:32.592
[solemn music]

01:32.625 --> 01:34.661
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:34.694 --> 01:36.729
[exhales]
Something else.

01:36.762 --> 01:39.265
Something I need to tell you.

01:39.899 --> 01:41.167
Okay.

01:41.200 --> 01:43.636
I don't want what happened
to me to happen to you.

01:43.669 --> 01:46.572
I've always wanted you
to have choice and freedom,

01:46.606 --> 01:48.108
shit I didn't have.

01:50.576 --> 01:51.845
I owe you that.

01:54.647 --> 01:57.350
I haven't been honest with you
about everything.

01:59.552 --> 02:01.454
A while ago you...

02:01.487 --> 02:03.823
You asked if I knew
where your father was,

02:03.856 --> 02:07.527
and...
I said I didn't, but...

02:08.828 --> 02:10.029
That was a lie.

02:10.062 --> 02:12.265
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:15.868 --> 02:17.570
Your dad is dead.

02:17.603 --> 02:19.606
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:20.773 --> 02:22.141
S... What?

02:22.174 --> 02:25.745
I should have told you before,
but I couldn't.

02:25.778 --> 02:28.281
-That's not--
-You wouldn't have
listened to me,

02:28.314 --> 02:30.183
and I wanted to help you,
to make things right--

02:30.216 --> 02:31.884
That's not...
that's not possible.

02:31.917 --> 02:33.252
It's not.
It's not possible.

02:33.285 --> 02:34.887
No, no, you don't know.

02:34.920 --> 02:36.422
You don't know, because I--

02:36.455 --> 02:38.258
I have been talking to him.

02:38.291 --> 02:40.326
Like, he and I...

02:40.359 --> 02:43.095
He left me a message yesterday.
He's looking for me.

02:43.129 --> 02:45.030
He's been looking for me
this whole fucking time.

02:45.064 --> 02:46.799
I'm sorry.

02:46.832 --> 02:48.835
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:51.270 --> 02:53.239
[whooshing]

02:53.272 --> 02:55.475
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:00.580 --> 03:01.781
Dad?

03:04.517 --> 03:05.852
Dad!

03:07.820 --> 03:09.189
Simon?

03:13.159 --> 03:14.394
Dad!

03:15.128 --> 03:16.296
Dad!

03:18.030 --> 03:19.199
Dad!

03:21.567 --> 03:22.735
Dad, please!

03:24.237 --> 03:25.705
[Nikolai] Henry.

03:27.206 --> 03:30.743
[tense music]

03:30.776 --> 03:32.679
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:38.184 --> 03:40.386
[panting softly]

03:40.420 --> 03:42.288
How do you know
about this place?

03:43.256 --> 03:44.390
This is my...

03:44.423 --> 03:47.260
this is my dad's cabin.

03:49.929 --> 03:51.831
[birds chirping]

03:56.101 --> 03:57.703
[dramatic musical flourish]

03:57.737 --> 03:58.805
No.

04:00.039 --> 04:01.341
It's my cabin.

04:03.776 --> 04:04.844
Henry...

04:08.081 --> 04:09.748
I killed him.

04:09.781 --> 04:13.118
It happened a long time ago,
before I even knew
you existed, I--

04:13.151 --> 04:15.288
No. No.

04:16.856 --> 04:19.859
That doesn't make any sense,
because...

04:21.193 --> 04:23.662
My body has been
taking me here.

04:23.696 --> 04:26.833
I've been dreaming
about him.

04:26.866 --> 04:29.368
We... we're connected.

04:29.401 --> 04:32.572
He is here!
He has to be here!

04:32.605 --> 04:36.042
Your dad is here,
in a way.

04:38.110 --> 04:40.212
It's where I buried him.

04:40.245 --> 04:43.649
[dark music]

04:43.682 --> 04:46.919
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:49.021 --> 04:50.256
No.

04:50.289 --> 04:52.058
[whooshing]

04:54.994 --> 04:55.962
Dad?

04:58.697 --> 05:00.032
Hank.

05:00.065 --> 05:01.534
[laughs]

05:01.567 --> 05:03.702
Oh, Hank.

05:03.736 --> 05:05.271
Hey.

05:05.304 --> 05:07.139
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

05:07.172 --> 05:10.176
It's okay,
it's okay.

05:10.209 --> 05:12.612
Everything is gonna be okay.

05:15.914 --> 05:17.950
[dark music]

05:17.983 --> 05:20.152
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:20.185 --> 05:22.088
[cries]

05:26.825 --> 05:28.961
[exhales]

05:28.995 --> 05:30.330
Why?

05:31.631 --> 05:32.598
Why?

05:34.834 --> 05:36.336
Huh?

05:37.270 --> 05:38.438
Why?

05:39.539 --> 05:41.139
Why?

05:41.173 --> 05:43.208
I did what I thought was right.

05:43.241 --> 05:44.343
[cries]

05:44.377 --> 05:47.346
<i> Your dad,
he wasn't like us.</i>

05:47.379 --> 05:48.715
He wasn't a teleporter.

05:49.816 --> 05:52.652
He was an Inactive.

05:53.518 --> 05:56.021
<i> And he was bitter about it.</i>

05:56.055 --> 05:57.824
<i> He made a choice.</i>

05:57.857 --> 06:00.593
<i> He was gonna tell whoever
would listen to him</i>

06:00.626 --> 06:02.295
<i> about people like us.</i>

06:02.328 --> 06:04.297
I couldn't let that happen.

06:04.330 --> 06:07.066
It was my job not to let
that happen.

06:09.101 --> 06:10.436
Be quiet.

06:11.003 --> 06:12.004
Daddy?

06:12.038 --> 06:13.439
[grunting]

06:13.472 --> 06:15.341
[crashing, whooshing]

06:15.374 --> 06:16.942
He was dangerous.

06:16.975 --> 06:18.710
If he would've known
what you would've become--

06:18.744 --> 06:20.045
No.

06:20.078 --> 06:21.748
[ragged breathing]

06:22.414 --> 06:23.682
[Simon]<i> Please.</i>

06:23.715 --> 06:25.250
Please.

06:25.284 --> 06:26.485
I have a family.

06:26.519 --> 06:28.354
-Me too.
-[gunshot]

06:28.387 --> 06:29.755
[gasps]

06:29.788 --> 06:31.791
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:36.262 --> 06:39.198
I trusted you.
[panting]

06:39.231 --> 06:41.134
You're a fucking liar!

06:41.968 --> 06:43.335
You're a liar!

06:43.369 --> 06:45.571
Fucking liar!

06:47.773 --> 06:50.476
[cries]
You let me think...

06:50.510 --> 06:54.446
[screams] You let me think
he was alive this whole time

06:54.480 --> 06:57.049
when you knew...
you knew what you did!

06:57.082 --> 06:58.350
You knew!

06:58.384 --> 07:00.419
[somber music]

07:00.452 --> 07:02.655
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:06.792 --> 07:09.862
[cries]
You knew the whole...

07:09.895 --> 07:11.898
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:18.904 --> 07:21.206
[crying]

07:21.240 --> 07:22.408
I'm sorry.

07:22.441 --> 07:24.777
[cries]
I need him.

07:25.578 --> 07:28.247
[leaves rustling]

07:28.281 --> 07:31.850
[cries] I need him.

07:31.884 --> 07:34.020
[tense music]

07:34.053 --> 07:36.121
-Henry...
-[sobbing]

07:36.154 --> 07:38.324
My dad...

07:38.357 --> 07:40.560
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:45.297 --> 07:47.133
You took him from me.

07:48.267 --> 07:50.102
-[snap]
-Ahhh!

07:55.307 --> 07:56.776
Henry, I...

07:56.809 --> 07:58.845
[whooshing]

08:03.215 --> 08:04.483
-[snap]
-Ahh!

08:04.516 --> 08:05.885
[both grunting]

08:05.918 --> 08:07.520
[whooshing]

08:07.553 --> 08:09.055
[both grunt]

08:11.390 --> 08:14.259
-[screams]
-[whooshing]

08:14.293 --> 08:16.062
[rattling]

08:17.296 --> 08:18.530
[tires screech]

08:18.563 --> 08:20.600
-[whooshing]
-[grunts]

08:21.601 --> 08:23.903
[both panting]

08:25.171 --> 08:27.940
[groaning]

08:31.377 --> 08:33.012
[gurgling]

08:34.079 --> 08:35.681
[pained grunting]

08:37.516 --> 08:39.151
Help.

08:39.184 --> 08:42.522
[panting]

08:44.022 --> 08:44.991
Henry...

08:45.958 --> 08:47.259
Why?

08:47.293 --> 08:48.694
Huh?

08:48.728 --> 08:51.030
What the fuck
were you doing with me?

08:52.264 --> 08:53.199
I...

08:54.400 --> 08:56.068
I care about you.

09:02.308 --> 09:04.277
[gasping]
Henry, Henry!

09:05.477 --> 09:07.946
Please...

09:07.980 --> 09:10.916
[solemn music]

09:10.949 --> 09:12.952
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:15.487 --> 09:18.057
[snapping, clattering]

09:19.491 --> 09:20.826
I'm done.

09:21.994 --> 09:24.931
[crackling]

09:28.133 --> 09:31.070
[wheezing]

09:33.172 --> 09:35.775
[Nikolai gasping]

09:40.245 --> 09:41.213
[moans]

09:42.414 --> 09:43.583
[gasps]

09:45.417 --> 09:48.688
[speaking other language]

09:49.988 --> 09:51.891
[crackling]

10:03.568 --> 10:06.038
[panting]

10:13.446 --> 10:16.382
[solemn music]

10:16.415 --> 10:18.618
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:19.545 --> 11:21.814
[phone beeping]

11:29.254 --> 11:31.691
[line trilling]

11:32.825 --> 11:34.860
[Elaine]
<i> I told you not to call me.</i>

11:36.929 --> 11:39.065
Your brother's dead.

11:42.501 --> 11:43.736
<i> Henry...</i>

11:45.837 --> 11:47.473
<i> He finally told you.</i>

11:51.677 --> 11:53.278
Keep this phone.

11:53.312 --> 11:55.246
<i> If you ever need anyth--</i>

11:55.280 --> 11:57.383
[beeping]

11:57.416 --> 11:59.418
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:18.838 --> 12:20.106
[door buzzes]

12:23.642 --> 12:25.444
I woke and you were gone.

12:26.345 --> 12:27.813
I couldn't stay.

12:30.149 --> 12:32.251
What I asked of you
was unfair.

12:33.985 --> 12:37.222
But I'm here now
to make amends.

12:37.255 --> 12:40.092
To act as a witness
on your behalf.

12:40.892 --> 12:42.828
This is not where you belong.

12:43.495 --> 12:45.564
But it is.

12:45.598 --> 12:47.966
Confessing to a crime
you did not commit

12:48.000 --> 12:50.335
will not provide relief
for your past sins.

12:50.369 --> 12:51.804
It's not about that.

12:51.837 --> 12:54.539
This is my path
to salvation.

12:54.573 --> 12:56.709
This is my purpose.

12:56.742 --> 13:00.846
What purpose can you possibly
serve from a cell?

13:02.814 --> 13:05.785
I know you, Lucas Boone.

13:07.153 --> 13:08.554
And you know me.

13:14.626 --> 13:16.328
I care for you.

13:31.609 --> 13:33.479
Job 4:15.

13:44.022 --> 13:45.957
"Fear came upon me,
and trembling,

13:45.991 --> 13:47.993
which made all
my bones to shake.

13:51.296 --> 13:54.266
Then a spirit passed
before my face..."

13:54.300 --> 13:56.435
"And the hair of my flesh
stood up.

13:58.937 --> 14:00.972
It stood still...

14:01.006 --> 14:03.241
but I could not discern
the form thereof:

14:03.275 --> 14:07.313
an image
was before mine eyes."

14:09.781 --> 14:12.418
This is your purpose?

14:15.320 --> 14:16.856
An angel?

14:19.257 --> 14:21.659
-I don't understand.
-I'm protecting her.

14:21.693 --> 14:23.061
Her?

14:23.094 --> 14:26.431
So this angel is alive?

14:26.464 --> 14:29.301
She... she came to you?

14:30.769 --> 14:32.938
Why would an angel
want this for you?

14:32.971 --> 14:35.474
She doesn't.

14:35.507 --> 14:37.041
I came to this on my own.

14:37.075 --> 14:39.611
Lucas, if you are here
to protect this angel,

14:39.645 --> 14:43.082
does that mean she is the one
who killed your father?

14:50.022 --> 14:53.425
[Townes]
Maybe she just lost it.

14:53.458 --> 14:54.827
In the barn?

14:54.860 --> 14:57.029
Where Nikolai dissolved
Bill Boone's body?

14:58.897 --> 15:00.933
What if he did something
to her?

15:00.966 --> 15:03.735
That's not possible.
Nikolai left Reston.

15:03.768 --> 15:05.871
At least that's
what Henry said.

15:05.904 --> 15:07.273
So what does that mean?

15:10.208 --> 15:12.443
-Do you think Henry could've--
-No.

15:12.477 --> 15:15.580
-Henry would never hurt Anna.
-I don't know.

15:15.614 --> 15:18.584
I mean, she convinced Lucas
to confess for her.

15:19.785 --> 15:20.919
How do you know that?

15:20.952 --> 15:23.288
-[door opens]
-Townes.

15:23.321 --> 15:25.491
[panting]

15:26.658 --> 15:28.027
My dad...

15:29.394 --> 15:31.063
He's dead.

15:32.030 --> 15:33.732
-What?
-Henry...

15:33.765 --> 15:35.067
[Henry]
I feel so stupid.

15:35.100 --> 15:36.435
I should've known.

15:36.468 --> 15:38.904
'Cause if he was alive,
he would've found me, right?

15:38.937 --> 15:41.373
I mean, he would've, like,
knocked on my door,

15:41.407 --> 15:42.440
but he couldn't.

15:42.474 --> 15:45.144
He couldn't, because Nikolai
fucking killed him.

15:45.177 --> 15:46.412
Nikolai?

15:46.445 --> 15:50.249
This whole time, I thought
that I was gonna see him again.

15:50.282 --> 15:54.019
But he's been dead, like,
most of my life.

15:56.288 --> 15:57.823
Henry, whose blood is that?

15:57.856 --> 15:59.891
[dark music]

15:59.924 --> 16:02.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:05.564 --> 16:07.433
What else happened?

16:09.901 --> 16:12.570
He killed my dad.

16:12.604 --> 16:16.008
Look, I didn't mean to, but I
couldn't just let him, like...

16:17.876 --> 16:20.412
He took him from me!

16:20.446 --> 16:22.013
Jenna, you know.

16:22.046 --> 16:23.214
You know what this feels like.

16:23.247 --> 16:25.651
I mean, with your mom, like...

16:25.684 --> 16:29.421
I lost him, and he...
he fucking deserved it!

16:30.021 --> 16:31.990
He deserved it!

16:32.024 --> 16:34.460
What about Anna?
What happened to her?

16:37.629 --> 16:39.031
What?

16:43.869 --> 16:45.337
Did you kill her too?

16:46.739 --> 16:48.774
-Where did you get that?
-The barn.

16:50.909 --> 16:52.378
Here.

16:53.679 --> 16:55.113
It's fine.
Just give it to me.

16:55.147 --> 16:56.848
No, why?
So you can destroy it?

16:56.881 --> 16:57.916
No, of course not.

16:57.949 --> 16:59.617
Where the hell is she?

16:59.651 --> 17:00.552
What did you do?

17:00.585 --> 17:02.954
-Nothing!
-Henry, did you hurt her?

17:02.988 --> 17:03.988
No!

17:04.022 --> 17:05.758
She's not fucking dead!
Sh--

17:09.394 --> 17:10.562
I just...

17:12.364 --> 17:14.366
I just...
I took her somewhere.

17:16.067 --> 17:17.502
I had to!

17:17.536 --> 17:20.439
She found out everything,
and I was...
I was protecting us.

17:20.472 --> 17:23.042
-Oh, my God.
-Where did you take her?

17:25.544 --> 17:26.878
Anna's a good person.

17:26.912 --> 17:29.447
She's not like Bill or Nikolai.

17:29.480 --> 17:32.684
This, this is not...
heroes don't do this!

17:32.717 --> 17:34.052
I'm gonna fix it.

17:34.085 --> 17:36.021
-Just give me the phone.
-No.

17:36.054 --> 17:37.790
Jenna, come on!
Someone could trace it!

17:37.823 --> 17:39.391
If Anna's okay,
it doesn't matter.

17:39.425 --> 17:40.925
Jenna, just--

17:40.959 --> 17:42.760
-Give it to me... Jenna.
-No!

17:42.794 --> 17:44.062
-Let go!
-Stop it!

17:44.095 --> 17:46.164
-Just let go!
-No!

17:46.197 --> 17:48.133
-Stop it!
-You don't get it!

17:48.166 --> 17:49.868
You don't fucking get it!

17:49.901 --> 17:52.036
-Ah!
-[Jenna] You're sick!

17:52.070 --> 17:54.339
Henry, there's something
wrong with you!

17:54.372 --> 17:56.942
-That's not true!
-You're a fucking monster!

17:56.975 --> 17:58.443
Don't fucking say that!

17:58.477 --> 18:00.112
Like Nikolai!

18:00.145 --> 18:02.080
-[rumbling]
-[Townes screams]

18:02.114 --> 18:04.316
-[shrieks]
-[high-pitched ringing]

18:06.651 --> 18:08.487
[screams]

18:10.021 --> 18:11.490
[gasping]

18:14.092 --> 18:15.827
[coughs]

18:15.861 --> 18:18.096
Nikolai killed Sam too,
didn't he?

18:18.129 --> 18:19.798
[gasps]

18:19.831 --> 18:21.700
You knew!

18:21.733 --> 18:24.436
You knew, and you lied to me.

18:24.470 --> 18:25.370
No. Please...

18:25.403 --> 18:27.305
please, just turn it off.

18:27.338 --> 18:29.141
Just turn it off.
[coughs]

18:33.812 --> 18:35.247
[ringing stops]

18:36.013 --> 18:37.816
[panting]

18:40.151 --> 18:42.321
I believed in you.

18:45.323 --> 18:46.658
[whispering]
I'm sorry.

18:48.794 --> 18:50.529
I'm so sorry.
Please...

18:52.163 --> 18:54.233
Please.

18:54.266 --> 18:56.735
-Please, Townes.
-Get out of my room.

18:56.768 --> 18:58.837
-Townes--
-Get out now!

18:58.870 --> 19:00.939
[panting]

19:00.972 --> 19:02.474
[gasps]

19:03.842 --> 19:05.543
[sniffles]

19:05.577 --> 19:07.445
I'm gonna bring her back, okay?

19:07.479 --> 19:09.648
I'm gonna fix it.
I promise I'm gonna fix it.

19:09.681 --> 19:11.783
I'm gonna--
I'm gonna fix all of it!

19:11.816 --> 19:13.385
[sniffling]

19:17.555 --> 19:19.291
[door shuts]

19:25.197 --> 19:27.132
[birds chirping]

19:27.165 --> 19:29.268
[exhales]

19:31.135 --> 19:33.238
[whooshing]

19:36.674 --> 19:37.676
Anna?

19:37.709 --> 19:39.811
[echoing] Anna?

19:39.844 --> 19:40.846
Anna!

19:40.879 --> 19:43.014
[echoing] Anna!

19:43.047 --> 19:44.249
Anna!

19:44.282 --> 19:45.817
[echoing] Anna!

19:48.020 --> 19:50.622
[dramatic music]

19:50.655 --> 19:52.624
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:56.194 --> 19:58.063
Oh, shit.

19:58.096 --> 19:59.431
Oh, God.

20:03.168 --> 20:04.836
Anna?

20:04.869 --> 20:05.971
Oh, God.

20:07.339 --> 20:10.309
[breathing heavily]

20:13.945 --> 20:16.448
[gasping]

20:16.481 --> 20:17.449
[gasps]

20:18.616 --> 20:19.951
[whooshing]

20:19.985 --> 20:22.654
-[grunts]
-[thudding]

20:30.095 --> 20:32.764
[panting softly]

20:35.534 --> 20:36.501
Mom?

20:46.644 --> 20:48.480
[sighs]

21:07.799 --> 21:09.267
[whispering] Shit.

21:09.300 --> 21:11.703
[soft dramatic music]

21:11.736 --> 21:13.739
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:04.856 --> 22:07.693
[low mechanical humming]

22:08.727 --> 22:11.295
-[latch clicking]
-[Wendy] Thank you.

22:11.329 --> 22:13.331
We'll see you next week.
Thank you.

22:13.365 --> 22:15.066
Goodnight.

22:15.099 --> 22:17.369
God bless.
Goodnight.

22:17.836 --> 22:19.304
Thank you.

22:19.337 --> 22:21.340
Mrs. Boone?

22:29.514 --> 22:30.916
It's Mrs. Jacobson.

22:32.417 --> 22:34.385
Is there something
I can help you with?

22:34.418 --> 22:39.290
I'm concerned
about your son, Lucas.

22:39.323 --> 22:41.993
I fear he may be following
the wrong path.

22:43.628 --> 22:45.430
I'm sorry.
How do you know him?

22:47.064 --> 22:49.400
We belong to the same church.

22:49.433 --> 22:51.536
I saw him this morning.

22:51.569 --> 22:54.639
He seems consumed
with a particular young woman.

22:54.672 --> 22:57.842
I'm hoping you can help me
find her.

22:57.876 --> 23:00.579
I believe she's connected
to your ex-husband.

23:03.314 --> 23:04.950
You know her...

23:06.451 --> 23:08.386
I'm sorry, I can't help you.
I have to get back--

23:08.419 --> 23:10.155
Mrs. Jacobson, please.

23:10.188 --> 23:12.758
Do not give up on him.

23:12.791 --> 23:15.827
I know all too well
what it's like to lose a son.

23:17.028 --> 23:20.965
Mine died too soon.

23:20.998 --> 23:24.302
But death is not the only way
to lose a child.

23:24.335 --> 23:27.739
A boy needs his mother.

23:29.508 --> 23:31.476
Now, please...

23:31.510 --> 23:33.512
who is the girl?

23:36.748 --> 23:39.050
[Cleo echoing]<i> I don't know.
I saw this place.</i>

23:39.084 --> 23:41.652
<i> It looked decent.
The people were nice.</i>

23:41.686 --> 23:45.023
<i> And they have egg rolls
which maybe is a sign.</i>

23:47.158 --> 23:48.460
Henry?

23:53.365 --> 23:54.966
You all right?

23:54.999 --> 23:56.134
[echo stops]

23:56.868 --> 23:57.836
Yes, yeah.

23:59.036 --> 24:01.406
I don't know if you noticed,
but I got some new bowls.

24:01.439 --> 24:05.310
I mean, they're just plastic,
but they're nice plastic,
right?

24:05.343 --> 24:06.944
And they're ours.

24:06.978 --> 24:08.580
[bowls rattling]

24:11.349 --> 24:12.817
You know, I was thinking,

24:12.850 --> 24:15.220
like, after everything
that's happened...

24:17.422 --> 24:19.491
Maybe we should just go.

24:20.057 --> 24:21.793
-Go where?
-Anywhere.

24:27.231 --> 24:30.001
I know this is a lot at once.

24:30.034 --> 24:31.702
But it's not the end.

24:31.736 --> 24:34.238
It's gonna get better.
It has to.

24:34.272 --> 24:35.607
We're just...

24:35.640 --> 24:40.479
we're deep in the shit
of, like, a bad thing, and...

24:42.580 --> 24:44.015
But we have each other.

24:44.049 --> 24:46.218
And we're gonna
get through it together.

24:47.051 --> 24:48.019
Okay?

24:49.253 --> 24:50.655
Okay.

24:54.925 --> 24:57.762
Hey, what if we have dinner
in bed?

24:57.796 --> 24:59.931
Dinner in bed is
always better, right?

25:00.999 --> 25:02.600
Come on.
Come on.

25:02.633 --> 25:05.136
We can pick out a movie
on your laptop.

25:05.169 --> 25:07.872
[both laugh]

25:07.905 --> 25:10.642
You know, but maybe...
maybe something a little more

25:10.675 --> 25:12.677
<i> Romy and Michele</i>
and a little less

25:12.711 --> 25:14.312
<i> Requiem for a Dream.</i>

25:14.345 --> 25:16.882
-Just saying.
-[chuckles]

25:19.284 --> 25:20.519
Here.

25:30.061 --> 25:31.729
Hey.

25:31.762 --> 25:33.598
You know I love you,
right?

25:35.166 --> 25:36.535
And I'm proud of you.

25:40.171 --> 25:41.573
I love you too.

25:43.908 --> 25:46.611
All right,
let's see what we got.

25:48.279 --> 25:50.015
[phone ringing in distance]

25:50.682 --> 25:52.083
This isn't me.

25:53.451 --> 25:55.987
[laughs nervously]
I mean, I don't...

25:56.020 --> 25:58.289
I don't even remember
writing this.

25:58.323 --> 26:00.258
I thought what I
turned in was...

26:02.694 --> 26:04.696
I don't know.

26:04.729 --> 26:07.432
Just, I want
to go to college.

26:07.465 --> 26:09.834
And I want to have a future,
so...

26:09.868 --> 26:13.271
please, just tell me
what to do, and I'll do it.

26:13.305 --> 26:16.574
I'll rewrite every essay,
I'll retake every test.

26:16.607 --> 26:18.043
-I'll--
-And then what?

26:19.911 --> 26:21.379
[stammers]

26:21.412 --> 26:22.714
What do you mean?

26:23.848 --> 26:25.650
[sighs]

26:25.684 --> 26:27.185
Are you okay?

26:28.886 --> 26:30.522
Yeah.

26:30.555 --> 26:32.257
Totally.
I'm fine.

26:33.524 --> 26:37.295
I mean, no, like,
because of this, but...

26:39.564 --> 26:41.733
Is there anything else
going on at home?

26:41.766 --> 26:43.901
I know what happened
with Bill Boone

26:43.935 --> 26:45.870
and your dad's girlfriend.

26:45.903 --> 26:47.572
Yeah, that's o... that's okay.

26:47.605 --> 26:49.340
I mean... I mean...

26:49.373 --> 26:51.109
it's not, but... but it is.

26:51.142 --> 26:52.844
It's fine.
I'm fine.

26:54.412 --> 26:55.546
Just give me another chance.

26:55.579 --> 26:57.315
I mean...
you know me.

26:57.348 --> 26:58.717
I'm a straight-A student.

26:58.750 --> 27:01.419
I'm not this person.
This isn't me.

27:01.452 --> 27:04.255
You've said that
a couple of times now.

27:06.123 --> 27:08.192
Look, Jenna,

27:08.226 --> 27:10.862
if you keep ignoring
what's going on with you,

27:10.895 --> 27:12.763
that something is going on,

27:12.796 --> 27:16.400
then things like this
will keep happening.

27:16.433 --> 27:18.870
You wrote those essays.

27:18.903 --> 27:21.639
You failed a number
of your tests.

27:21.673 --> 27:24.009
No one else.
You.

27:25.709 --> 27:28.746
It's okay not to be okay.

27:28.780 --> 27:32.117
But ignoring it
won't make it any less real.

27:35.320 --> 27:38.189
[video game gunfire]

27:41.393 --> 27:44.061
[gun clicks,
video game gunfire]

27:44.095 --> 27:45.096
[knocks on door]

27:46.197 --> 27:47.298
[man screams]

27:47.331 --> 27:48.233
[gun clicks]

27:49.967 --> 27:51.836
Hey, what's up?
You need something?

27:53.138 --> 27:54.872
[video game gunfire]

27:54.906 --> 27:58.543
Uh, the housekeeper
wants to move to Wednesdays,

27:58.576 --> 28:00.344
so I thought
we could switch your PT

28:00.378 --> 28:03.247
so that you didn't have
to work around her.

28:03.280 --> 28:05.049
Okay, cool.
Whatever.

28:05.083 --> 28:08.586
[gun clicks,
video game gunfire]

28:08.619 --> 28:10.688
Uh, Mom, I'm in the middle
of a game.

28:10.722 --> 28:12.991
[video game gunfire]

28:17.728 --> 28:19.297
[game beeps]

28:19.330 --> 28:20.832
Okay.

28:22.033 --> 28:23.201
What?

28:26.937 --> 28:31.076
When I was a sophomore
in college, I dated a swimmer.

28:31.109 --> 28:32.911
Uh, not for long,

28:32.944 --> 28:35.813
and "dating" is probably
too strong a word,

28:35.846 --> 28:37.715
but we went out a few times.

28:37.748 --> 28:40.719
He was older than me,
but only by a year.

28:41.152 --> 28:42.887
Anyway, uh...

28:42.920 --> 28:47.024
we... we were at a party...

28:47.057 --> 28:50.227
one night,
and we were drinking.

28:50.261 --> 28:51.696
But not a lot.

28:51.729 --> 28:56.501
Um... and we ended up
in one of the rooms.

28:57.869 --> 29:00.204
I don't even remember how,
but...

29:00.238 --> 29:02.273
And we were kissing.

29:02.306 --> 29:06.111
And then it got to a point
where I...

29:06.144 --> 29:07.845
tried to stop it.

29:07.878 --> 29:10.881
Politely at first, and then...

29:10.914 --> 29:13.885
less so, but he didn't listen.

29:21.325 --> 29:24.028
After that, this boy and I
stopped talking.

29:26.063 --> 29:29.767
We never talked about
how we stopped talking.

29:29.800 --> 29:31.769
I would see him

29:31.803 --> 29:34.572
around the campus
here and there, and...

29:34.606 --> 29:36.407
every time, I, uh...

29:41.245 --> 29:44.816
You see, my generation,
we didn't talk about
this sort of thing.

29:49.053 --> 29:51.289
I knew right away
how it made me feel.

29:51.322 --> 29:54.159
It just took longer
to put a word to it.

29:55.693 --> 29:58.163
To realize that
what happened to me...

30:01.832 --> 30:03.001
was rape.

30:05.069 --> 30:07.705
I've never told anybody
what happened.

30:07.739 --> 30:09.240
Not your father.

30:10.441 --> 30:11.843
Not Robert.

30:13.144 --> 30:16.213
I don't know
if I was afraid, or...

30:16.247 --> 30:17.749
ashamed, or--

30:17.782 --> 30:19.416
Then why are you telling me?

30:19.450 --> 30:22.420
[somber music]

30:22.453 --> 30:24.522
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:27.391 --> 30:28.860
I think you know why.

30:31.829 --> 30:34.032
I don't have a fucking clue,
actually.

30:36.700 --> 30:38.169
Then why won't
you look at me?

30:38.202 --> 30:40.338
Get the fuck out
of my room.

30:43.674 --> 30:45.877
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:06.197 --> 31:09.167
In the end, you have to live
with what you've done.

31:10.735 --> 31:14.072
It'll be between you and God,
and you can't escape Him.

31:24.481 --> 31:25.450
[door slams]

31:29.253 --> 31:32.023
-[door opens]
-[indistinct chatter]

31:32.790 --> 31:35.627
[indistinct chatter,
laughter]

31:54.011 --> 31:55.479
What are you doing here?

31:55.512 --> 31:56.915
You okay?

31:58.148 --> 32:00.551
[whispering]
Are you okay?

32:00.585 --> 32:02.220
Yeah, of course.

32:03.921 --> 32:05.256
Jesus.

32:05.990 --> 32:08.426
This is so fucked up.

32:12.430 --> 32:14.932
[whispering] I'm the one
who should be in here.

32:14.966 --> 32:17.368
Not you... I'm the one
who should be in here.

32:17.401 --> 32:20.137
I'm gonna tell them...
I'm gonna tell them the truth.

32:20.170 --> 32:21.739
I'm gonna tell them
that it was me,

32:21.772 --> 32:22.907
and we're gonna get you
out of here.

32:22.940 --> 32:24.275
-Henry, no, no. No.
-Yes.

32:26.010 --> 32:27.679
This is what I want.

32:28.746 --> 32:29.980
And I get it, I do.

32:30.014 --> 32:32.450
I have been where you are,
questioning who I was,

32:32.483 --> 32:33.885
believing there was
no good in me,

32:33.918 --> 32:35.386
but the very fact
that you're questioning it...

32:35.419 --> 32:37.021
that means
there is good in you.

32:37.055 --> 32:40.824
I am...
I am not an angel, Lucas.

32:40.857 --> 32:42.093
-I'm not.
-[exhales sharply]

32:42.126 --> 32:44.061
I let you believe that I was

32:44.094 --> 32:46.664
so that you would help me,
but I am not.

32:46.697 --> 32:49.934
I am a bad and selfish person.

32:49.967 --> 32:51.469
Hey.
Hey, hey.

32:53.671 --> 32:55.540
You are not.

32:56.907 --> 32:59.176
You're not.

32:59.210 --> 33:01.846
What, you think all angels
are perfect and shit?

33:01.879 --> 33:04.849
You gotta read the Bible,
because that's not
what they are,

33:04.882 --> 33:06.718
and that is not
who I think you are.

33:06.751 --> 33:09.220
I'm not that fuckin' crazy,
Henry.

33:09.253 --> 33:10.455
I'm not.

33:12.189 --> 33:13.657
I killed your father.

33:13.690 --> 33:16.327
You also walked through fire
without getting burned.

33:16.361 --> 33:17.562
Jesus Christ.

33:19.163 --> 33:22.600
-Sorry, I'm just...
-I know. I know.

33:22.633 --> 33:24.268
It's a lot to take in.

33:26.537 --> 33:28.205
[whispering] I...

33:28.239 --> 33:31.041
I don't... I don't know
what you want from me.

33:31.075 --> 33:33.110
I don't--I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

33:33.144 --> 33:35.179
Could you please...

33:35.212 --> 33:37.849
Look, it took me
getting away from here

33:37.882 --> 33:40.618
and all my family shit

33:40.651 --> 33:42.086
to finally see clearly,

33:42.119 --> 33:44.822
to see what I was meant for,
but I know it now.

33:44.855 --> 33:47.492
I fuckin' know it
right in here.

33:48.859 --> 33:50.394
And I've got faith

33:50.428 --> 33:54.966
that if you can just
clear all this noise...

33:54.999 --> 33:57.001
that you'll know too.

33:57.034 --> 34:00.805
The Lord will open a path
for you, Henry.

34:03.073 --> 34:05.209
But you gotta
open your eyes to see.

34:06.444 --> 34:08.645
[indistinct chatter,
laughter]

34:08.679 --> 34:11.048
[tense music builds]

34:11.081 --> 34:12.550
You shouldn't be here.

34:17.088 --> 34:18.656
You gotta go.

34:18.689 --> 34:20.057
-Okay?
-Lucas.

34:20.090 --> 34:21.425
Wait.
Come on.

34:21.458 --> 34:23.294
Hey. Just...

34:23.327 --> 34:25.063
[sighs]

34:26.396 --> 34:28.733
Remember that doing
what's right...

34:30.834 --> 34:32.836
Isn't always what's easy.

34:32.870 --> 34:35.606
[moody music]

34:35.639 --> 34:37.642
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:47.485 --> 34:48.719
[Thomas] Hey.

34:48.752 --> 34:49.886
[door shuts]

34:49.920 --> 34:51.589
That was a really long meeting.

34:52.856 --> 34:56.160
Yeah, I've... I've been
driving around for a while.

34:59.430 --> 35:01.965
Okay, so?
How did it go?

35:01.999 --> 35:03.534
Did you guys come up
with a plan?

35:03.567 --> 35:05.536
You gonna get
your grades back up?

35:08.272 --> 35:10.441
We mostly just talked about me.

35:12.776 --> 35:13.844
Cool.

35:13.877 --> 35:14.879
Okay.
Got it.

35:18.816 --> 35:19.750
That's it?

35:19.783 --> 35:21.819
-What do you want me to say?
-I don't know.

35:21.852 --> 35:23.620
More than that.

35:23.654 --> 35:25.756
Come on, Jenna, I...

35:25.789 --> 35:28.525
[scoffs] It feels like
I can't win with you. You...

35:28.559 --> 35:30.494
[sighs] I'm trying
to make things right.

35:30.527 --> 35:33.430
I'm trying to put you first,
try to get you out
of this mess,

35:33.463 --> 35:35.766
-get you back
to your old self--
-What does that mean?

35:37.168 --> 35:39.604
[sighs] I don't know.
I don't... ah...

35:40.671 --> 35:42.439
-I'm just talking.
-No, you do know.

35:42.472 --> 35:44.375
-You're just not saying it.
-[sighs heavily]

35:44.408 --> 35:47.110
That... I can't
keep doing this with you.

35:47.144 --> 35:49.880
-You make it so hard.
-How do I make it hard?

35:49.914 --> 35:50.915
You're afraid.

35:52.349 --> 35:54.752
You're afraid to talk
about Mom.

35:54.785 --> 36:00.023
You're afraid to get mad
and, like, actually
feel things,

36:00.057 --> 36:02.660
and you're afraid
to know who I am.

36:02.693 --> 36:04.728
Like, really know me.

36:04.762 --> 36:06.831
That's not true.
Not true.

36:06.864 --> 36:09.199
Aren't you still trying
to figure out who you are?

36:09.232 --> 36:11.101
I mean, you're just 17.

36:11.134 --> 36:12.770
[sighs]

36:16.507 --> 36:17.475
Right.

36:35.392 --> 36:38.528
-Look who I found.
-Mom, you have to knock.

36:38.562 --> 36:39.630
Hi.

36:39.663 --> 36:41.699
I like your room.

36:41.732 --> 36:43.267
It's bigger in person.

36:43.300 --> 36:45.570
It's larger
than Megan's room too.

36:46.837 --> 36:47.838
Mom?

36:47.872 --> 36:49.440
Some privacy?

36:50.007 --> 36:51.274
Oh, yes.

36:51.308 --> 36:53.276
Sorry.
Of course.

36:53.310 --> 36:55.312
But game night
starts in ten,

36:55.346 --> 36:57.481
and we don't hold your spot
if you're late.

36:57.514 --> 36:59.316
[laughs]
I'm just kidding.

36:59.349 --> 37:01.551
I...
That's a joke.

37:01.585 --> 37:02.887
Ah.

37:02.920 --> 37:04.555
But seriously, ten minutes.

37:04.588 --> 37:07.191
Your father and I will
shuffle the board.

37:07.224 --> 37:08.826
[door shuts]

37:14.197 --> 37:16.233
I have something
important to tell you.

37:16.266 --> 37:18.803
Is it about the allergens here?
Because your mom already
said that--

37:18.836 --> 37:21.672
Nope, it's actually
highly sensitive information.

37:22.907 --> 37:25.676
But I need your permission
before I say more,

37:25.709 --> 37:29.246
because I don't want
to burden you with my problems

37:29.280 --> 37:31.348
unless you want
to be burdened.

37:31.382 --> 37:32.850
I love you, Townes.

37:33.717 --> 37:34.918
Whatever you need,

37:34.952 --> 37:36.854
whatever's going on,

37:36.887 --> 37:38.021
I'm in.

37:38.055 --> 37:39.290
All right.

37:40.691 --> 37:41.626
So...

37:42.727 --> 37:45.796
For some time now,
I've been acting as a sidekick

37:45.829 --> 37:47.632
to a superhero.

37:49.333 --> 37:50.600
-Oh.
-I know.

37:50.634 --> 37:53.804
It's been very exciting, but...

37:55.773 --> 37:59.109
Then something
terrible happened.

37:59.142 --> 38:01.879
Really terrible, and...

38:01.912 --> 38:06.016
now I think maybe
I've actually been a henchman,

38:06.050 --> 38:09.420
serving not a hero
but a villain.

38:10.287 --> 38:12.823
I... I don't know
what I am or...

38:12.856 --> 38:14.725
or who I'm meant to be.

38:14.758 --> 38:18.362
All I know is, I need to try
and make things right.

38:21.198 --> 38:22.867
Lives are on the line.

38:24.034 --> 38:25.369
-Okay.
-And...

38:25.402 --> 38:27.938
I want you to be my partner.

38:27.971 --> 38:29.673
Not a sidekick.

38:29.706 --> 38:32.943
But my equal
in this fight,

38:32.977 --> 38:34.378
if there is a fight.

38:34.412 --> 38:38.015
But hopefully there's not,
and if there is,
it's nothing too physical.

38:38.049 --> 38:39.884
[chuckles]
Um, yeah, I hope so too.

38:39.917 --> 38:40.918
Yeah.

38:43.053 --> 38:45.855
Well, good, great.

38:45.889 --> 38:46.957
Thank you.

38:46.991 --> 38:48.759
Mm.

38:48.792 --> 38:50.727
[stammers]
I love you too, by the way.

38:50.761 --> 38:53.097
-I forgot to say it before.
-[laughs]

38:55.132 --> 38:56.666
Okay, there's a lot
to explain,

38:56.700 --> 38:58.636
but our first mission
is time-sensitive.

38:59.536 --> 39:01.505
I need you to help me
find someone.

39:03.540 --> 39:05.576
She could be anywhere
in the world.

39:08.012 --> 39:10.681
[dramatic music]

39:10.714 --> 39:12.717
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:54.257 --> 39:55.926
Dad's gone?

40:01.065 --> 40:02.533
I'm sorry.

40:04.434 --> 40:07.438
I'm so sorry for everything.

40:09.340 --> 40:12.409
I think I let you down.
[cries]

40:12.442 --> 40:15.746
I know that this isn't
what you wanted.

40:16.713 --> 40:19.250
This isn't
who you wanted to be.

40:19.283 --> 40:20.584
And I'm just...

40:23.620 --> 40:25.689
I just don't know
